                <h1>Discover the Rich History of New Orleans</h1>
                <p>New Orleans, founded in 1718, has a rich history marked by a blend of French, Spanish, and African influences. It became a vital port city due to its strategic location along the Mississippi River. Known for its vibrant culture, music, and cuisine, New Orleans has evolved through wars, disasters, and civil rights movements, remaining a unique American city.</p>
